quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,247,"And their prophet said to them, "
  2,248,"And their prophet said to them, ",1:[Signs giving reassurance.]
  2,249,"And when Saul went forth with the soldiers, he said, "
  3,187,"And [mention, O Muḥammad], when Allāh took a covenant from those who were given the Scripture, [saying], "
  3,188,"And never think that those who rejoice in what they have perpetrated and like to be praised for what they did not do - never think them [to be] in safety from the punishment, and for them is a painful punishment."
  3,189,"And to Allāh belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth, and Allāh is over all things competent."
  4,127,"And they request from you, [O Muḥammad], a [legal] ruling concerning women. Say, ",1:[i.e., their rights, in general, and their mahr, specifically.]
  4,128,"And if a woman fears from her husband contempt or evasion, there is no sin upon them if they make terms of settlement between them - and settlement is best. And present in [human] souls is stinginess.{1} But if you do good and fear Allāh - then indeed Allāh is ever, of what you do, Aware.",1:[i.e., holding on to self-interests.]
  4,129,"And you will never be able to be equal [in feeling] between wives, even if you should strive [to do so]. So do not incline completely [toward one] and leave another hanging.{1} And if you amend [your affairs] and fear Allāh - then indeed, Allāh is ever Forgiving and Merciful.",1:[Neither divorced nor enjoying the rights of marriage.]
  5,64,"And the Jews say, ",1:[Implying inability to give or stinginess.]
  5,65,"And if only the People of the Scripture had believed and feared Allāh, We would have removed from them their misdeeds and admitted them to Gardens of Pleasure."
  5,66,"And if only they had upheld [the law of] the Torah, the Gospel, and what has been revealed to them from their Lord [i.e., the Qur’ān], they would have consumed [provision] from above them and from beneath their feet.{1} Among them are a moderate [i.e., acceptable] community, but many of them - evil is that which they do.",1:[i.e., in great abundance.]
  6,25,"And among them are those who listen to you,{1} but We have placed over their hearts coverings, lest they understand it, and in their ears deafness. And if they should see every sign, they will not believe in it. Even when they come to you arguing with you, those who disbelieve say, ",1:[When you recite the Qur’ān.]
  6,26,"And they prevent [others] from him and are [themselves] remote from him. And they do not destroy except themselves, but they perceive [it] not."
  6,27,"If you could but see when they are made to stand before the Fire and will say, "